'''Holsworthy Community College''' is a [[Mixed-sex education|coeducational]] [[Foundation school|foundation]] [[secondary school]], located in [[Holsworthy, Devon|Holsworthy]] in the [[English county]] of [[Devon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.holsworthycollege.devon.sch.uk/ |title=Holsworthy Community College |publisher=Holsworthycollege.devon.sch.uk |date= |accessdate=2014-05-02}}</ref>

Previously a [[Community school (England and Wales)|community school]], Holsworthy Community College became a foundation cooperative trust school on 31 August 2012 as part of a federation with [[Okehampton College]].<ref name="devon1">{{cite web|url=http://www.holsworthycollege.devon.sch.uk/index.phtml?d=522335 |title=About Us |publisher=Holsworthycollege.devon.sch.uk |date= |accessdate=2014-05-02}}</ref> [[Devon County Council]] coordinate admissions to the school, which is mainly from 12 feeder primary schools.

Holsworthy Community College offers [[General Certificate of Secondary Education|GCSEs]], [[Business and Technology Education Council|BTECs]] and [[Cambridge Nationals]] as programmes of study for pupils. The school was awarded specialist [[Technology College]] status on 1 September 2006 which funded a science and technology extension to the building.<ref name="devon1"/>

